    {
        "url": "/quotes/michael_specter_634079",
        "quote": "We inherit every one of our genes, but we leave the womb without a single microbe. As we pass through our mother's birth canal, we begin to attract entire colonies of bacteria. By the time a child can crawl, he has been blanketed by an enormous, unseen cloud of microorganisms - a hundred trillion or more.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Michael Specter",
            "url": "/quotes/michael_specter_634079"
